        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks CD for new edition of <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> [4th ed. (1866)].</p>  
<p>Comments on CD’s criticism of the harsh tone of <hi rend="italic">Generelle Morphologie</hi>. Thinks he may have harmed himself but not the cause. Believes a radical reform of the science necessary, and since most scientists take a prejudiced view of the matter, a vigorous attack is essential.</p> 
            <p>Describes his travels in Canaries, Spain, and France.</p>
        </abstract>
